TY  - JOUR
AU  - Berkman, Henk
AU  - McKenzie, Michael D.
AU  - Verwijmeren, Patrick
T1  - Hole in the Wall: Informed Short Selling Ahead of Private Placements*
PY  - 2017
Y1  - 2017/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfw036
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 21
IS  - 3
SP  - 1047
EP  - 1091
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Companies planning a private placement typically gauge the interest of potential buyers before the offering is publicly announced. Regulators are concerned with this practice, called wall-crossing, as it might invite insider trading, especially when the potential investors are hedge funds. We examine privately placed common stock and convertible offerings and find evidence of widespread pre-announcement short selling. We show that pre-announcement short sellers are able to predict announcement day returns. The effects are especially strong when hedge funds are involved and when the number of buyers is high. We also observe pre-announcement trading in the options market.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfw036
ER  - 



